The article discusses the importance of promoting democratic values and good governance in the Summit of the Americas. It highlights that this has been a core component of the summit since its inception in 1994. The leaders at the Third Summit in 2001 articulated the principles that would later be embodied in the Inter-American Democratic Charter and pledged to fight corruption that undermines democratic governance at the Eighth Summit in 2018. The upcoming summit, with the theme "Building a Sustainable, Resilient, and Equitable Future," aims to continue this tradition. The article emphasizes that the administration and its partners will work towards fortifying democratic institutions, investing in civil society, strengthening independent media, and implementing a regional digital transformation that is transparent and equitable.